REFERENCE: If it drops to $\theta_{\text{user}}$ or below, Pass becomes possible (subject to the posterior). This is why adaptive sampling can eventually reach Pass even when early calibration shows an elevated floor. \subsection{Adaptive Batching} \label{app:batching}
Type: ❓ unverified
Details: Reference could not be verified

RAW REFERENCE TEXT:
As sampling continues, $\theta_{\text{floor}}(n)$ decreases. If it drops to $\theta_{\text{user}}$ or below, Pass becomes possible (subject to the posterior). This is why adaptive sampling can eventually reach Pass even when early calibration shows an elevated floor.

\subsection{Adaptive Batching}
\label{app:batching}

================================================================================
